Exercise 7.1: Typography Utilities (display-1, lead, text-muted, fw-bold, etc.)
HTML Example:
<div class="container mt-4">
  <h1 class="display-1">Welcome to the Event Portal</h1>
  <p class="lead">This portal helps you browse and register for upcoming events effortlessly.</p>
  
  <p>This is a <span class="fw-bold">bold</span> statement and this is <span class="text-muted">muted text</span>.</p>

  <p class="fs-4">This is a slightly larger text using <code>.fs-4</code></p>
  
  <p class="fst-italic">This paragraph uses <code>.fst-italic</code> to display italicized text.</p>
</div>

Exercise 7.2: Text Transformation Utilities (text-uppercase, text-lowercase, text-capitalize)
 HTML Example:
<div class="container mt-5">
  <p class="text-uppercase">this text is uppercase</p>
  <p class="text-lowercase">THIS TEXT IS LOWERCASE</p>
  <p class="text-capitalize">this sentence is capitalized automatically</p>
</div>
